    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2011 BMW M3 (E92), featuring the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving masterpiece utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS technology to achieve an 8,400 RPM redline. Power is managed by a lightning-quick 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch transmission and a variable M differential lock, providing unparalleled mechanical grip and exit speeds. The chassis is bolstered by Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and remains in factory-spec alignment. This vehicle boasts a comprehensive service history, including preventative rod bearing replacement and reinforced throttle actuators. The finish is flawless, and the interior retains its original factory texture, representing a true collector-quality example of the final naturally aspirated M3.",
